<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1942,2041]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="564" pageId="6" pageNumber="563">
“Head, pronotum and scutellum pale fuscous brown; scutellum with a black spot at each basal angle, the lateral margins ochraceous, widened before apex; abdomen above pale fuscous brown, posterior segmental margins ochraceous, the apical segment nearly wholly ochraceous; body beneath and legs pale ochraceous, tibiae black; head, face and pronotum thickly coarsely punctate, scutellum more finely punctate; tegmina with the basal and claval areas semiopaque, ochraceous, and obscurely finely granulate” (
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[806,955,189,216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" pagination="1 - 248" refId="ref8266" refString="Distant, W. L. (1916) Rhynchota- Homoptera: Appendix. In: Shipley A. E. &amp; Marshall, G. A. K (Eds.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma, 6, pp. i-viii + 1 - 248." type="journal article" year="1916">Distant 1916</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="564" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis box="[199,362,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer with dorsoposterior angle more angularly produced than more rounded and shorter posteroventral angle. Aedeagus with one pair of symmetrical subapical lateral processes, each process distally slightly widened and spiculate, process of dorsal apodeme as long as dorsal apodeme and stouter than shaft. Other characters as in generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis box="[199,361,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Measurements</emphasis>
. Male 
<quantity box="[441,528,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
long, 2.0 mm wide across eyes and 
<quantity box="[939,1026,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
