<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,513,539]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[322,484,513,539]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" pagination="602 - 609" refId="ref8229" refString="Distant, W. L. (1912) Rhynchota notes-liv. Annals and Magazine Natural History, 10 (8), 602 - 609. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222931208693279" type="journal article" year="1912">Distant (1912)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on unknown number of speciemens (syntypic) collected from “Tenasserim Valley; Myitta (Doherty, Brit. Mus.)”; there is one 
<typeStatus box="[929,1016,549,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">syntype</typeStatus>
in the BMNH which is designated as 
<typeStatus box="[151,257,585,611]" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1912" box="[270,473,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Radhades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassus">
<emphasis box="[270,473,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="564">Radhades crassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1115,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="564" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ulopinae">Ulopinae</taxonomicName>
by the cylindrical body, the short and anteriorly rounded crown and the foretibiae dorsally scored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
